## Add Lakebase GraphDB engine (Postgres)

Context: Pluggable graph backend alongside LadybugDB. Admins pick **Settings â†’ Graph DB**: internal Ladybug (`.lbug` + optional Volume sync) or **Lakebase** flat triple tables on the App-bound Postgres instance (`graph_engine` / `graph_engine_config`). Factory-only dispatch keeps engines mutually exclusive; SQL-only path uses existing `TripleStoreBackend` defaults + `SWRLSQLTranslator`.

Changes:

1. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/__init__.py`
   Export Lakebase modules and `LAKEBASE_AVAILABLE` when `psycopg` is present.
2. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/pool.py`
   Process-wide pool for graph workloads with JWT-aware Lakebase auth.
